# Project Design System

## Overview

Define the product's visual identity here before implementation. Describe mood, density, audience, and the type of trust the UI should create.

## Colors

- Primary is used for core text and major headings.
- Secondary is used for metadata and lower-emphasis labels.
- Accent is reserved for primary actions and active states.
- Danger is reserved for destructive or urgent states.

## Typography

Use headline-lg for hero or major page headings. Use body-md for main reading text. Use label-sm for metadata and compact controls.

## Layout

Use a consistent spacing rhythm. Group related controls in cards or sections. Avoid decorative spacing that is not tied to hierarchy.

## Elevation & Depth

Prefer borders and tonal surfaces over heavy shadows unless the product design specifically calls for depth.

## Shapes

Use rounded.md for controls and rounded.lg for cards. Avoid mixing many radius values.

## Components

Primary buttons use the accent token. Cards use the surface token and project spacing values.

## Do's and Don'ts

Do use the defined tokens. Do not introduce new hardcoded colors or fonts inside UI components without first updating this file.
